comments.body: We have a use case!  Steve Ferguson has been working with MVWs in his Lapidus Collection.  He tries to ensure he sets OCR for every child in the sequence, but setting it once in the parent would be so helpful to him and would reduce human error opportunities. I see this becoming a problem if setting it in the parent is the only way to set OCR for a MVW (some vols/items may have different lanugages within the MVW)?

pul_solr.title: The main collection of catalog-staging does not include alma

comments.body:
To replicate:

Request https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C0365_c0194, https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C0714_c025, and https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C0714_c026

It only happens if two items get combined within a box, and there's another box in another call number. The ones that are going to get combined have to be at the top of the parameters for the bug to replicate.

We need to look into the parameters that get sent in this case. We have a theory that it's falling back to the ItemTitle with no request number.
